SIMPLE: important
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Important
<hw>Im*por"tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>important</ets>. See <er>Import</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of, or burdened by, import; charged with great
interests; restless; anxious.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou hast strength as much⟦br⟧
As serves to execute a mind very <qex>important</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Carrying or possessing weight or consequence; of
valuable content or bearing; significant; weighty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Things small as nothing . . . ⟦br⟧
He makes <qex>important</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Bearing on; forcible; driving.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He fiercely at him flew,⟦br⟧
And with <qex>important</qex> outrage him assailed.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Importunate; pressing; urgent.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Weighty; momentous; significant; essential;
necessary; considerable; influential; serious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>important-looking</ent>⟦br⟧
